# Bilingual README (VaultClip)

This repository maintains **two** user-facing README files at the repo root:

| File | Language | Audience |
|------|----------|----------|
| `README.md` | English | Default; bundled in the app Resources |
| `README.ru.md` | Russian | Russian readers |

## When to update

Whenever you change **user-visible behaviour**, **security**, **installation/build steps**, **keyboard shortcuts**, **data paths**, or **project structure** documented in README:

1. Update **both** files in the same change.
2. Keep section structure aligned (same headings, tables, code blocks).
3. Preserve cross-links at the top:
   - `README.md` → `**Русский:** [README.ru.md](README.ru.md)`
   - `README.ru.md` → `**English:** [README.md](README.md)`
4. Keep the upstream [Yippy](https://github.com/mattDavo/Yippy) fork credit in both files.
5. Use **Contact** / **Контакты** with `aleksey@karakuts.com` per workspace contact rules.

## Do not

- Put Russian-only prose in `README.md` or English-only prose in `README.ru.md` (except proper nouns, paths, and keyboard symbols).
- Update only one README when the other would become stale.
- Add `README.ru.md` to the app bundle unless explicitly requested — only `README.md` is copied into Resources.
